broccoli beef.review:
Just as I was settling in to cook a delicious birthday dinner for the cutest boy in san francisco, my stove top freaked out and wouldn't light. What's a girl to do? Call Yum Yum Hunan to save the day!

Literally, we couldn't stop chanting "YUM YUM HUNAN" during our meal...which devolved into "NOM NOM HUNAN" pretty quickly. A feast of sweet & sour pork, honey walnut prawns, broccoli beef, chicken chow mein, and steamed rice was at my doorstep less than 1/2 hour after I called. {Note: you don't need this much food for two people. I will have leftovers for weeks. Hilariously, they included 5 fortune cookies, as if to say "no way this is for a couple."}

Everything was perfectly cooked, fresh, and was piping hot even post-delivery. Thank you YYH!

